rComments: Ron is literally the sweetest man you could possibly have as a prof. His lectures are far from boring (he doesnt post the notes so you do have to go), he shows genuine care for his students too. Always so excited to talk about the topics. Also his exam was very easy and he makes it near impossible for you to fail. Miss that guy.
LECTURES ARE VERY INTERESTING, TUTORIAL ATTENDANCE IS MANDATORY BUT EXAM IS VERY ESSAY AS LONG AS YOU USE THE STUDY GUIDE HE PROVIDES!

Ron Leprohon is an amazing professor who cares about how you feel as a student. He is super clear, caring and helpful. Attendance is mandatory for tutorials not for classes however, he makes classes really interesting so I'd recommend you to go.

Professor Leprohon made Egyptology so interesting for someone who had no prior knowledge of the subject. Amazingly passionate and a fantastic lecturer. The course is not difficult because he truly wants you to enjoy Egyptology. Best prof and class I've had as a Life Sci student! Got an A in this course. 100% recommended!

Prof Lep is extremely passionate and very nice. He is very clear about the fact that he doenst throw curve balls on the exam (which he didnt). Readings aren't mandatory. Just study off study guide and synthesize it with class notes and review past exams for a nice 90% on exam.

rComments: Professor Leprohon is THE BEST lecturer I've had in UofT. He's caring, puts his students' interest in mind, and actually replies to email (and pretty quickly at that, too). He made CLEAR guidelines of what will come out in the exam, so as long as you follow it, you will have 0 difficulty in the actual exam. But you MUST come to lectures to pass.

rComments: Professor Leprohon is by far the most caring, genuine, and supportive professor I've ever had. I can honestly say I will never forget him as a prof. rComments: Wow, just wow! This man is an amazing professor, and he is the reason why I decided to have a major in NMC.
